body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to SecureCars. My name is Dylan Miller. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Amanda. Can you please provide me with your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my date of birth is two five zero five one nine seven eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Amanda. Could you also provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, the last four digits are nine eight seven two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Amanda. We will look into the security issue at the Car Dealership. Is there anything else you would like to add?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I'm feeling relieved that it's being addressed. Thank you!

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Amanda. Thank you for your time and for reporting this matter. Have a great day.
